body:
With current code next example fails since counter starts at wrong value.
Bug is noticed due to fact that all FFs are aldffs when imported trough Verific.

```
[options]
mode bmc
multiclock on
depth 2

[engines]
smtbmc boolector


[script]
read -formal aldff.v
prep -top aldff

[file aldff.v]
module aldff(
input clk
);
parameter WIDTH=10;

reg [3:0] f_count;

initial f_count = 1;
always @(posedge clk)
if (f_count == WIDTH-1)
	f_count <= 0;
else
	f_count <= f_count + 1'b1;

always @(*)
	assert(f_count < WIDTH);

endmodule
```

